<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Workers Urged to Support Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Top Chinese trade union leader
today urged the country's workers to show understanding to and
support the country's reform efforts, correctly handle the
relationship between national and personal interests, and play an
exemplary role in safeguarding social stability.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, chairman of the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions, made this remark this afternoon, at a major gathering
marking the upcoming May 1 International Labor Day in the Great
Hall of the People in downtown Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"State-owned enterprises are the pillars of China's national
economy. The Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee
plans to help most state-owned large and medium-sized enterprises
that are suffering losses now to overcome their economic
difficulties within a period of less than three years," said Wei,
who is also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
To attain this goal, he said, it is indispensable to have the
enthusiastic support and active involvement of the broad masses of
the workers, who constitute the "fundamental propelling force" for
the reform.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the massive layoffs by state enterprises in
recent years to duplicated or aimless construction, poor
enterprise management and the irrational employment system and
policies under the planned economy long practiced in China.
</P>
<P>
"To raise the efficiency of enterprises by laying off their
redundant workers should be regarded as an inevitable historical
step, which, fundamentally speaking, is conducive to economic
growth and in line with the long-term interests of the working
class," he noted.
</P>
<P>
However, he conceded that this step has also been causing
temporary difficulties for some Chinese workers.
</P>
<P>
"Whether we can find a good solution to the problems in the
lives and re-employment of the laid-off workers has a bearing not
only on the success of state enterprise reforms, but also on the
consolidation of social stability and the socialist system," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He urged Party committees and governments at all levels to make
painstaking efforts and take effective measures to ensure the
basic living standards of the laid-off workers, especially those
experiencing difficulties.
</P>
<P>
"Our Party's principle of wholeheartedly relying on the working
class must be unswervingly adhered to at all times and under all
circumstances," said Wei, adding that trade unions across the
country should be guaranteed full support in performing their
basic duty of safeguarding workers' legitimate rights and
interests, as well as the right to work independently according to
law.
</P>
<P>
At today's gathering, the All-China Federation of Trade Unions
also announced its decision to honor 1,000 model workers and 300
model work units, which has become a regular ritual performed
around each year's Labor Day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
