<HEADLINE> De Bruin Rejects Drugs Allegations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Ireshi triple Olympic gold
medallist Michelle De Bruin Wednesday rejected drugs allegations
levelled against her by swimming's governing body FINA, according
to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
"I will fight this all the way," De Bruin, who could be banned
for life if found guilty of tampering with a doping sample, told a
Dublin news conference.
</P>
<P>
Gunnar Werner, general secretary of FINA, said earlier
Wednesday the 28-year-old De Bruin had manipulated the sample of a
random test she undertook in January. 
</P>
