<HEADLINE> China Lose to U.S. 59-80 in Four-Nation Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Winless China suffered another
defeat when they lost to the United States 59-80 at the
four-nation women's basketball tournament here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
China, runners-up at the 1994 world championship, were
overwhelmed by the higher, faster and stronger American women and
had increasingly poorer shooting percentage in the second half.
</P>
<P>
"We played only the first half well," Chinese head coach Ma
Yuenan said.
</P>
<P>
The reigning Olympic champions United States improved to a 4-1
record in the double round-robin tournament.
</P>
<P>
Australia tied the American women with a same record after
beating Japan 81-64.
</P>
<P>
On the final day of the tournament Thursday, Australia take on
China, and the United States face Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
