<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Members Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC) here today approved the list of
members of the Preparatory Committee of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The preparatory committee will be set up in May this year, with
its headquarters here.
</P>
<P>
Five natives of Macao were elected as vice-chairmen of the
preparatory committee, among whom is Ho Hau Wah, a 43-year-old
industrialist. Ho is also a member of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Ho said that the preparatory committee, including leaders from
all walks of life in Macao, will make decisions in accordance with
the long-term interests of the people of Macao, who will surely
support the work of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's successful return to the motherland will assist the
members of the preparatory committee to carry out their duties, Ho
noted.
</P>
<P>
Macao will become a special administrative region under the
concept of "one country, two systems" after its return to
China on December 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The members of the committee from China's interior area are
quite familiar with Macao affairs, and have cooperated with their
counterparts from Macao in drafting the Basic Law of the Macao
SAR, Ho said.
</P>
<P>
He further noted that the existing friendly cooperation between
the governments of China and Portugal is a key to the smooth
transition of Macao. He expressed the hope that the two
governments would continue their sound cooperation in the coming
years.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the Preparatory Committee will start
work right away on tackling the temporary economic difficulties
and slow progress of localization of civil servants in Macao,
problems which have aroused the serious concern of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Ho said, the duty of the committee is to make
preparations for the future Macao SAR government, and Macao people
should also rely on themselves to solve some of their problems.
</P>
<P>
It is a challenge and an opportunity for Macao people to show
their wisdom and courage to work for a better future for Macao,
Ho said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
