<HEADLINE> UEFA Doubles Campaign Money to Boost Johansson's Chance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- European soccer body UEFA will
double the campaign money to 800,000 Swiss Francs to boost its
president Lennart Johansson's bid for the FIFA presidency.
</P>
<P>
UEFA Finance Committee Egiduis Braun said UEFA had agreed to
double the cash available after FIFA General Secretary Sepp
Blatter declared his candidacy earlier this month, according to
reports reaching here from Dublin on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Braun said the increase "is valid and justifiable" because 50
European countries "want Johansson as FIFA President."
</P>
<P>
The FIFA Congress will convene in Paris on June 8 when 200
nations vote for the new president for the international governing
body of the sport of soccer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
