Strauss-Kahn said that "there is no peril in the field" for
France's state Giat Industrie land arms producing company, which
is reducing staff and spending to cut deficit.
</P>
<P>
The Giat Industrie, which produces tanks, artillery pieces and
rifles, lost 467 million francs (77 million U.S. dollars) in 1997,
compared with 2.1 billion francs (350 million dollars) in 1996.
