<DOCNO> XIE19980430.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oxford Falls Down at UK University Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Oxford, Britain's world famous
academic institution, has fallen behind some less famous
universities in the country to rank the third at the UK university
premier league, according to a survey published Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The first Financial Times survey of UK higher education found
that Oxford, Britain's once undisputed intellectual powerhouse,
has fallen behind not only Cambridge but in some respects also the
less famous London's Imperial College.
</P>
<P>
The table established by the survey recorded performance across
16 categories, ranging from entrance requirements to library
expenditure and a total score has been calculated.
</P>
<P>
The survey indicated that Cambridge beats Oxford in almost
every department, with tougher entry requirements, a better
teaching and research record and a higher proportion of research
students.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the survey signals the end of Oxford's
stranglehold on the higher education system and could spark new
calls for urgent reform in the institution.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Peter North, a former vice-chancellor of
Oxford, has earlier said that the university was at risk unless it
modernized. 
</P>
