<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Israel will ask U.S. Vice
President Al Gore to prevent Russia from providing nuclear
technology to Iran, said an Israel government official here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
David Bar-Illan, advisor to Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu,
told the Israel Radio that the Israeli side will raise this issue
with Gore during his visit here, and ask him to pressure Russia to
stop providing such technology to Iran.
</P>
<P>
Israel can not allow Iran to seek and develop such technology
because it will pose direct threat to Israel's national security,
Bar-Illan said.
</P>
<P>
"Mr Gore is personally in charge of this issue and could do
something to prevent Russia from providing nuclear technology to
Iran," he added.
</P>
<P>
Gore is expected here Thursday to attend Israel's 50th birthday
celebrations. He will hold talks with Netanyahu and the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) President Yasser Arafat on ways to break
the impasse of the Israeli-Palestinian peace talks.
</P>
<P>
In the Israeli cabinet, Industry and Trade Minister Natan
Sharansky is recently in charge of the Russian-Iranian nuclear
technology issue. He traveled to Russia and the United States in
the past months aimed at trying to stop the Russian-Iranian deal.
</P>
<P>
Israel claimed that Russia has provided such nuclear technology
which could help Iran develop nuclear and ballistic missiles, but
could not give any evidence in this regard. 
