<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hamas Vows not to Cede Inch of Palestinian Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Palestinian Islamic
Resistance Movement (Hamas) Leader Sheikh Ahmad Yassin Wednesday
vowed to continue struggle against Israel and not to give up any
Palestinian soil.
</P>
<P>
"We have made a pledge ... that we will not cede even an inch
of the Palestinian land to the enemy," Yassin said at a meeting
with Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi, Iran's official news
agency IRNA reported .
</P>
<P>
Despite all the problems and the U.S. support for Israel, he
said, bound by the slogan "Victory or Martyrdom," the Hamas would
continue struggle until the liberation of Palestine and freedom
from "the occupiers' oppression."
</P>
<P>
Yassin stressed that the liberation of Palestine requires
patience, perseverance and sacrifice, saying that "this is a goal
we hope to achieve through divine blessings and the spiritual
support by world of Islam."
</P>
<P>
He termed the Oslo peace accord between Israel and the
Palestinians as "one-sided accord," saying the accord has helped
the Palestinians realize that liberation of Jerusalem is possible
only through a struggle against the Israeli occupation and
oppression.
</P>
<P>
The Hamas leader also praised Iran for its "outstanding stands
and spiritual support for Palestinian people's struggle to
liberate their lands."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kharrazi reiterated Iran's "spiritual support for
the Palestinians," expressing hope that the Palestinian nation,
through unity and support by the Islamic world, would achieve the
sacred goal of liberating all the occupied lands.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian problem has figured prominently in Iranian
foreign policy since the Islamic revolution in 1979, he said,
Palestine and the Al-Qods (Jerusalem) have always had a place in
the hearts of the Iranian nation.
</P>
<P>
Iran arrived here Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
