<HEADLINE> European Youth Ministers Conference Ends in Bucharest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The fifth conference of the
European ministers responsible for the youth ended here Wednesday,
highlighting the efforts deployed in clarifying the role the youth
are playing in today's societies, as well as their integration
into the modern society.
</P>
<P>
Education, its recognition and the starting of a dialogue
between generations for the insurance of a better and harmonious
social climate added up to the solutions put forth for finding the
resources necessary for the implementation of youth programs.
</P>
<P>
The participants underscored the necessity for education
flexibility to narrow inequality of chances on the labor market.
</P>
<P>
The participants agreed that special programs for combating
racism, violence, xenophobia and intolerance would enable the
youth to take a more active part in the Public affairs, which in
turn would help systems and mentalities to change.
</P>
<P>
The next conference of the youth ministers, scheduled to take
place in Greece, is expected to endorse a European charter of
youth's rights. 
</P>
