escape, but his wife and six children, including babies, were
hacked to death by the criminals using axes, machetes, and
knives.
</P>
<P>
In a similar development, there have been reports of people
fleeing their homes in the communes of Buringa, Nyakabanda,
Nyabikenke and Rutobwe because of insecurity and harassment by
suspected Hutu militias. 
