<HEADLINE> U.S. Warplane Crashes in Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Navy EA-6B warplane
crashed in Saudi Arabia Wednesday but the four crew members
parachuted to safety, the Pentagon said.
</P>
<P>
The EA-6B, part of a fleet of allied warplanes keeping watch on
southern Iraq, crashed about 22 km north of Prince Sultan Air
Base, the Pentagon said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
It was the second crash of a U.S. military jet in the Gulf
region this week.
</P>
<P>
A Navy F/A-18 fighter based on the aircraft carrier
Independence crashed in northern Gulf Monday but the pilot was
recovered safely. 
</P>
</TEXT>
