<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Brazilian Privatization Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Washington, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank announced here
Wednesday the approval of a 170 million U.S. dollar loan to
finance a privatization project in the state of Minas Gerais, one
of four state government privatization projects in Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Three other projects are being carried out successfully in the
states of Rio Grande do Sul, Rio de Janeiro, and Mato Grosso.
</P>
<P>
The latest project reinforces the state government's structural
reform program with the objective of selling two state-owned
deposit-taking banks.
</P>
<P>
This project will also support the state's concession program,
which will make more efficient gas delivery operations and highway
maintenance services and includes the privatization or
concessioning of GASMIG (Companhia Estadual de Gas de Minas
Gerais), the state-owned gas company.
</P>
<P>
State programs supported by the project also include
concessioning of 460 kilometers of state roads, development of an
adequate regulatory framework for the private provision of public
services, and improvement of fiscal performance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
