<HEADLINE> 5 Soldiers of South Lebanese Army Wounded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Five members of Israel's ally
South Lebanese Army (SLA) were wounded Wednesday evening in
attacks by the Hezbollah in south Lebanon, the Lebanese Voice of
the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The casualties were caused at 20:00 local time (1700 GMT) when
the Muslim resistance force bombed SLA's Taier Harfai position in
the west of south Lebanon occupied by Israeli troops, the radio
said.
</P>
<P>
Two days ago, the area witnessed the most bloodiest fight
between the Hezbollah, or Party of God, and the Israeli troops
this year, which left a Hezbollah fighter dead, six Israeli
soldiers, an SLA member and three Lebanese civilians wounded.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a so-called security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 to allegedly protect its northern areas from cross-border
attacks by Muslim guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon's resistance forces have been fighting to drive the
Israeli troops and the SLA out of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Heavy casualties of Israeli troops have prompted the Jewish
state to seek a conditional withdrawal from south Lebanon through
negotiating security arrangements with the Lebanese government.
</P>
<P>
But Lebanon has rejected Israel's offer, insisting that the
withdrawal be unconditional. 
</P>
