<HEADLINE> Israeli-Angolan Ties Greatly Enhanced: Israeli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Ambassador to Angola
Tamar Golan said here Wednesday that the cooperation between the
two nations "has been greatly enhanced" in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Golan told the press that since Israel opened its embassy in
Angola in July 1995, great progress has been made in their
cooperation in politics and economics, especially in such fields
as telecommunications, aviation, agriculture, diamond and
petroleum.
</P>
<P>
Israel is helping the Angolan government in its effort to
resettle the demilitarized soldiers, the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
She said that there is a broad prospect in their cooperation
in diamond industry because Israel with advanced technology has
rich experience in the exploitation and sales of diamonds.
</P>
<P>
As for the petroleum sector, NEFTA, an Israeli oil company, is
negotiating with the Angolan government. The company is seeking
the right for jointly exploring petroleum with the Angolan
state-owned oil company.
</P>
<P>
Israel has provided Angola with high-tech irrigation equipment
and helped the southern African country to train its technicians,
said Golan.
</P>
<P>
In agriculture, a joint venture has been launched in the
suburb of Luanda.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, she said, her government also offers scholarships
for the Angolan officials to study in Israel. Some members of
the opposition National Union for Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA) and some local government officials have received
professional training in Israel since April 1997 when the
government of national unity and reconciliation was established.
</P>
<P>
Golan also noted that four Israeli specialists have come to
Angola to work with the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF)
in removing mines in some provinces of the country. And Israeli
mammalogist Tamar Ron has come to help the Angolan Environment
Ministry in conserving the endangered animal species.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli ambassador called on UNITA to make greater efforts
to accomplish all tasks stipulated in the 1994 Lusaka Peace
Protocol. She said that the two warring sides should continue
their efforts to avoid a reccurrence of war.
</P>
<P>
She believed that peace will be achieved finally in Angola and
it will brighten the future of the Israeli-Angolan cooperation.
</P>
</TEXT>
