<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
ended mixed Wednesday, with London and Frankfurt extending
Tuesday's gains to finish higher and Paris closing down on
profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE-100 index closed up 26.5 points or 0.46 percent
at 5,833.1, lifted by a firmer start on Wall Street after hovering
between small gains and losses for most of the session.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that a cautious trend was evident throughout the
session but the market took comfort from a steady performance on
Wall Street during afternoon trading.
</P>
<P>
Lloyds was hit by a downgrading, pulling other banks lower in
its wake.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German shares enjoyed solid demand and closed up
89.81 points or 1.79 percent at 5,108.48, with heavyweight
Deutsche Telekom posting considerable gains.
</P>
<P>
However, on the Paris bourse, the CAC-40 index closed weaker,
down 43.30 points or 1.15 percent at 3,733.93, as investors took
profits after Tuesday's rise of almost 2.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the prospect of a long holiday weekend also
caused the market to consolidate. 
