<HEADLINE> IMF Approves Third Annual Loan Under ESAF for Chad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) approved Wednesday the third annual loan under the
Enhanced Structural Adjustment Facility (ESAF) equivalent to 22
million U.S. dollars to back Chad's economic program for 1998-99.
</P>
<P>
The loan is available in two equal semiannual installments, the
first of which will be made available on May 6, this year.
</P>
<P>
The government's economic program for 1998-99 is aimed to
strengthen macroeconomic adjustment, with a view to reduce
financial imbalances and achieving sustainable growth.
</P>
<P>
The key macroeconomic targets of the program include: to
achieve annual real GDP growth of 6 percent, limit annual
inflation to 3.5 percent and contain the current account deficit
at 17 percent of GDP in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The ESAF is a concessional IMF facility for backing member
countries that are undertaking economic reform programs to
strengthen their balance of payments.
</P>
<P>
Chad joined the IMF in July 1963. Its quota is about 56 million
dollars equivalent and its outstanding use of IMF financing
currently totals about 59 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
