<HEADLINE> Illinois Plant Recalls Suspected Contaminative Beef </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- An Illinois ground beef plant
is recalling more than 127,120 kilograms of ground beef after
tests found samples contaminated with dangerous E. coli bacteria,
the U.S. Agriculture Department said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The recalled amount represents the day's production at an IBP
Inc. plant in Geneseo, Illinois, on April 14, the day an
Agriculture Department routine test found the contamination, the
department's spokesman Andy Solomon said.
</P>
