<HEADLINE> Zambia Revenue Authority lntensifies Effort to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia Revenue Authority
(ZRA) has intensified effort to curb smuggling and ensures that
all duties and other taxes are paid, Zambia News Agency ZANA
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Enoch Kavindele, minister of commerce, trade and industry,
quoted by ZANA, said on Wedanesday morning that as a result of
intensified patrols by a ZRA's flexible anti-smuggling team, an
additional revenue of one billion Kwacha or 700,000 U.S dollars
was realised in March.
</P>
<P>
In March, said the minister, one truck carrying grossly
undervalued goods while another one with 190 motorcar tyres were
seized by ZRA at the Kafue check point, 40 kilometers south of
Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
Kavindele added that ZRA will seize all the goods together
with the trucks used in these activities and in addition, severe
penalties and fines will be imposed on those involved.
</P>
<P>
He said the Zambian government is committed to seeing that ZRA
forces the law without any political interference.
</P>
<P>
In recent months, smuggling has increased at the borders,
putting many manufacturing companies in Zambia in a difficult
situation as their products can not compete favourably with
smuggled goods, which are priced much lower than the local ones.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last month, Britain gave Zambia a grant of about
14 million dollars and international tax and customs experts
began arriving in the country to assist ZRA to curb the
ever-rising cross-border smuggling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
