<HEADLINE> Underwater Mine Dormant for 60 Years Detonated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- An underwater mine which was planted
in the Yangtze River 60 years ago was successfully detonated at
three o'clock this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The mine, a relic of World War II, recently happened to be
found floating on the surface near Ezhou City, in central China's
Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The detonation was conducted by local People's Liberation Army
(PLA) troops under the direction of the Hubei Provincial
Government.
</P>
<P>
There are estimated to be more than 1,000 undiscovered
underwater mines on the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze
River, said Shen Guangyuan, an expert on the subject.  
</P>
</TEXT>
