<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ground Experiments on Space Vehicles Successful in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- China has made remarkable
progress in research and experiments on the ground testing of
carrier rockets, according to the Chinese Academy of Launch
Vehicle Technology (CALVT).
</P>
<P>
A series of advanced experimental equipment -- as well as
facilities to produce, store and transport low-temperature rocket
propellants -- has been installed at the Beijing Research
Institute of Experimental Technology under CALVT, making the
institute a leading space technology base for ground experiments
in China.
</P>
<P>
The institute has successfully conducted simulated ground and
high-altitude tests on rocket motors adapting conventional or
low-temperature fuel, and experiments on whole systems and parts
of rockets and satellites, said Zheng Jiwen, director of the
institute.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, simulated experiments on high-altitude ignition of
engines controlling the attitudes of satellites, as well as the
orbit-shifting engines, have also been carried out repeatedly,
Zheng said.
</P>
<P>
The director claims that the institute has now mastered the
world's most advanced technologies in collecting and processing
computerized data, which can help provide accurate, reliable and
real-time data for the experiments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
