<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-President's East Asia Tour Complete Success: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The just-ended visit to Japan and
the Republic of Korea (ROK) by Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao is
a complete success, a senior Chinese official said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dai Bingguo, head of the International Liaison Department of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, told reporters
that the visit has met the targets of extending friendship,
increasing understanding, enhancing trust, providing orientation
for the future, and furthering Sino-Japanese and Sino-ROK
cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
Hu, during his tour, exchanged sincere and wide-ranging views
on how to build a stable long-term and good neighborly
relationship between China and the two countries, said Dai, who
accompanied Hu on the visit.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan confirmed that the two countries must comply
with the principles and spirit enshrined in the Sino-Japanese
Joint Statement and the Sino-Japanese Peace and Friendship Treaty,
Dai said.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan agreed to seize upon opportunities, draw
lessons from history, and work together so as to establish a
long-term and stable relationship oriented toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
China and South Korea have also reached consensus on how to
bring a vigorous, long-term, stable and cooperative relationship
into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Hu briefed Japanese and South Korean business leaders on
China's economic situation and reform and opening-up measures.
The Chinese vice-president also discussed with them how to expand
economic, trade and technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Japan and South Korea commended China's responsible attitude
regarding the Southeast Asian financial crisis. They all agreed
to help each other overcome the temporary difficulties brought
about by the financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
The three countries pledged they would boost economic and trade
ties and achieve common prosperity and development on a mutually
beneficial basis, said Dai.
</P>
<P>
Dai said Japan and South Korea are China's major neighbors.
Developing good-neighborly ties and expanding cooperation is in
the interest of the three countries and is also conducive to
peace, stability and development in Asia and the whole world.
</P>
<P>
Dai believed that Hu's visit will eventually pose a significant
influence in developments between the three countries in the
impending new century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
