<HEADLINE> SSE Composite Index Hits New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange
(SSE) Composite Index climbed to a new high today since June, to
close at 1343.45 points, up 2.15 percent compared with last week.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the SSE 30 Index went up by a slight 0.78 percent,
against last week's figure, to close at 3836.16 points.
</P>
<P>
The bourse will not be open tomorrow because of the May Day
holiday; trade will resume May 4, according to the exchange.
</P>
<P>
The four trading days this week -- Monday to Thursday --
witnessed a total trading volume of 28.18 billion yuan, and of the
437 listed shares, 291 buoyed up.
</P>
<P>
The b-share trading also went up this week, to close at 51.61
points, with a total trading of 990 million yuan-worth. Of the 50
b-shares listed on the exchange, only nine fell.
</P>
<P>
The trading funds soared to 3.08 billion yuan, nearly 1.14 billion
yuan more than the figure for last week, though the number of
trading days was one day less than last week. Eleven of the
exchange's 16 funds moved upwards.
</P>
<P>
Also this week, bond trading reached 28.69 billion yuan on the
exchange. 
