<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Links German Businesses with East Asia: German Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The German government attaches
great importance to Hong Kong's function as a part of China and,
at the same time, a part of the international economy, a senior
German government official said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Gunter Rexrodt, federal minister of economics of Germany, who
is on a two-day visit to Hong Kong, said that German companies in
Hong Kong play an important role by linking German business with
China and the other countries in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
"With over 500 addresses, they still form the largest German
business community in the Far East and it is hard to imagine
German economic relations with eastern Asia without them," Rexrodt
said at a reception held Thursday in the Conrad Hotel in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Rexrodt, who arrived in Hong Kong at noon time on Thursday
following his visit to Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou, hosted the
reception to Hong Kong businessmen and foreign businessmen in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Rexrodt said that it is always stimulating and instructive to
end -- or to begin -- a visit to China in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's dynamism has become a symbol of the vigorous
development in eastern Asia over the last 20 years, Rexrodt said.
</P>
<P>
In what is currently a troubled region, Hong Kong is an anchor
of stability, he added.
</P>
<P>
With its stable currency, its high currency reserves and its
rock-solid budget, Hong Kong has supported the crisis management
of the International Monetary Fund (IMF) with an impressive
contribution.
</P>
<P>
As to his visit to China's inland areas, Rexrodt said that
following his discussions with representatives of the Chinese
government, he is sure that China is on the right track.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned companies are being restructured, the banking
system is being over-hauled, and the government apparatus is being
rejuvenated.
</P>
<P>
"I have no doubt that this new phase of the economic reforms
will be just as successful as the previous one," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should also recognize the great sense of responsibility for
the region shown by China during the present crisis," Rexrodt
stressed.
</P>
<P>
China is participating in the IMF's support measures. And it
has kept the external value of its currency stable, thus
preventing a race to devalue, he said.
</P>
<P>
Before the reception, Rexrodt held a press briefing to inform
reporters on his visit to China including Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At the press briefing, Rexrodt said that the German government
encourages German companies to expand their business in Asia,
especially in China's inland areas and Hong Kong, and invites Hong
Kong businessmen to invest in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Rexrodt met with Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) and Donald Tsang,
financial secretary of the SAR on Thursday afternoon. He is
scheduled to leave Hong Kong for home tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
