<HEADLINE> Russia Opposes New Sanctions Against Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia is opposed to the new
economic sanctions the Contact Group imposed on Yugoslavia, a
Russian foreign ministry spokesman said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Rakhmanin said the six-nation Contact Group should
instead focus attention on promoting political dialogue between
Belgrade and ethnic Albanian leaders.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Contact Group, which include the United States,
Russia, France, Britain, Germany and Italy, met in Rome on
April 29 to discuss the escalating Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
In a statement after the meeting, the group, with the exception
of Russia, decided to freeze Yugoslav assets abroad and threatened
to impose harsher sanctions if Belgrade fails to ease tensions in
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"Only With political dialogue, not economic sanctions, can the
international community dissolve the Kosovo crisis," Rakhmanin
said. 
</P>
