<HEADLINE> Legislative Council Election Forums Hold in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A number of Hong Kong
Legislative Council election forums for geographical
constituencies began to be held here from April 30 to May 21.
</P>
<P>
Local residents are invited to attend the forums organized by
district offices which will offer the electorate an opportunity to
gain a better understanding of the platforms of the candidates
running in their respective constituencies.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is divided into five geographical constituencies of
Hong Kong Island, Kowloon West, Kowloon East, New Territories West
and New Territories East, which will produce 20 Legislative
Council members through direct election on May 24.
</P>
<P>
The forums will include a self-introduction by the candidates,
a summary of their political platforms and floor discussions.
</P>
<P>
The Legislative Council will be composed of 60 members with 30
to be elected from functional constituencies and 10 from the
800-strong Election Committee except 20 from geographical
constituencies.
</P>
<P>
After deducting seven withdrawals and two invalid nominations,
there are now a total of 166 candidates of which, 156 will contest
for 50 seats of the Legislative Council except 10 from functional
constituencies has automatically become Legislative Council
members because the number of nominations is equivalent to that of
the allocated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
