<HEADLINE> India's Textile Export Falls Short of Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 30 (Xinhua) -- India's textile exports
increased by 4.6 percent in the just-ended financial year of
1997-98 but fell short of the 13.56 billion U.S. dollar target by
7.3 percent, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported Thursday.
</P>
