<HEADLINE> New Tour Brings Visitors to Landmarks in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Starting from Thursday,
visitors can join a new tour package by simply walking with
earphones on and a guidebook in hand to go through major landmarks
in Hong Kong in their own pace.
</P>
<P>
The package is the first of a series of "do-it-yourself" (DIY)
Heritage &AMP; Architecture Walks for both local residents and
overseas visitors wishing to learn more about Hong Kong's
historical development.
</P>
<P>
The new tour, launched by the Hong Kong Tourist Association
(HKTA), covers Hong Kong Island, and similar tours covering
Kowloon and the "New Territories" will be available later this
year and next year.
</P>
<P>
Armed with pre-recorded commentary from the portable audio
"Gallery Guide" and a practical walking guidebook featuring
information about all the sites on the tour, participants can
complete the walk at their own pace and discover some of the most
historic as well as modern landmarks in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The tour incorporates some of the area's most spectacular
architecture. These include the stately Legislative Council
(formerly known as Supreme Court) and St. John's Cathedral (the
oldest Western ecclesiastical building in Hong Kong), the Bank of
China Tower, and the Citibank Plaza.
</P>
<P>
The tour has been made possible with the support of the
Heritage &AMP; Architecture Advisory Board and funding from the
Tourism Development Fund recently granted by the Government of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
