<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preparatory Committee Won't Be 2nd Power in Macao: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MACAO, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official in Macao
said here on Thursday that the Macao Special Administrative Region
Preparatory Committee (SARPC) will constitute no second political
power in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch and
SARPC vice-chairman, made these remarks to reporters after meeting
with SARPC members from Macao in the morning.
</P>
<P>
The name list of the SARPC was adopted and issued by China's
National People's Congress on Wednesday. The 100-strong committee
has 60 members from Macao and 40 from China's inland.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side will respect the administration of the
Portuguese side before the handover on December 20, 1999 in Macao,
which is stipulated in the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration
signed in 1987," Wang said. "We have made and will continue to
have effective cooperation with Portuguese side. The SARPC will
constitute no second political power in Macao."
</P>
<P>
The director noted the SARPC Macao members represent all walks
of life in Macao, adding he believed that they will all do their
best to help in the preparation for the establishment of the Macao
SAR.  
</P>
</TEXT>
