<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France's Unemployment Rate Continues Downward Trend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- France's unemployment rate
continued to inch down in March by 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate dropped slightly to 12 percent from 12.2
percent in February, said the ministry of employment Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Except for a slight rebound in January, the unemployment rate
in France has been falling since last September.
</P>
<P>
The jobless number declined to below three million for the
first time since January 1996 when it was at 2,989,800.
</P>
<P>
The number of the unemployed below 25 dropped by 2.2 percent in
March, compared with 0.4 percent of those above 50, while those
considered long-time unemployed slumped by 1.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
France is expected to create a total of 400,000 jobs in 1998
and 1999, and the unemployment rate will continue to drop, said
Dominique Strauss-Kahn, minister of industry, finance and economy.
</P>
<P>
The drop in unemployment, he said, is due to the economic
policy of the socialist government. He did admit that there are
still too many unemployed in France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
