<HEADLINE> DPRK Freighter Sinks in Collision with Chinese Vessel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A freighter of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) sank in the southern part of the
Yellow Sea early Wednesday morning, after being in a collision
with a Chinese cargo ship, according to local official sources.
</P>
<P>
One DPRK sailor went missing and two others were injured in the
mishap.
</P>
<P>
The other 33 DPRK sailors were rescued by the Chinese vessel,
the "Yanglin".
</P>
<P>
The 15,123-dwt DPRK vessel was on its way from Yantai, in east
China's Shandong province, to Chittagong, Bangladesh, while the
13,637-dwt Chinese vessel, belonging to the Guangzhou Branch of
the China Ocean Shipping Co. was sailing on the way for Tianjin
from Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
A rescue vessel sent by the Shanghai Offshore Safety Bureau
took the two injured men from the "Yanglin" and gave them
emergency treatment. They were then transferred to the Shanghai
Sailors' Hospital for observation.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said that the two are now in stable condition.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the collision is still under investigation, but
local authorities have warned of bad weather conditions, including
thick fog.  
</P>
</TEXT>
