<HEADLINE> Public Servants' Salary Raised in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The minimum monthly salary for
Mozambican public servants would be raised from 311,297 Metical
(about 27 U.S. Dollars) to 353,886 Metical (about 30.5 dollars)
starting from April 1.
</P>
<P>
The decision was announced Wednesday by the government,
according to Noticias daily Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The highest salary for public servants below ministerial
level, has been hiked from 297.5 Dollars to 397 Dollars, a 55
percent increase.
</P>
<P>
University teachers, technicians working for public services,
and secretaries general at government departments are the main
beneficiaries of this hike.
</P>
<P>
Luisa Diogo, Deputy Minister for Finance and Planning, said
about 33,000 people working at grass-root education and health
units are also covered by the pay readjustment, with an increase
ratio of 29 percent.
</P>
<P>
The salary hike is aimed at attracting professionals to stay
in government departments, Diogo said.
</P>
<P>
About 95,000 employees are now working with the government
institutions.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the highest salary of some of the public
servants were about 18 times that of the lowest in 1991, and with
the new readjustment the disparity has been narrowed down to 9.6
fold. 
</P>
