<HEADLINE> FINA Upholds Comeback of Semifinal System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- World swimming body FINA will
not change its mind over the implementation of semifinal system
for teh 2000 Olympic Games, a top official said in Sydeny on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
FINA secretary Gunnar Werner said he had received a letter from
Australian Swimming asking for the delay of the return of
semifinals, which were last used at the 1980 Moscow Games.
</P>
<P>
"I'm sorry to say that we won't be changing it," Werner said
before leaving at the end of a three-day meeting with Olympic
officials. "We have made our decision and that's final."
</P>
<P>
FINA decided earlier this year it would reintroduce semifinals
for 50, 100 and 200 meters events as a way of making the sport
more exciting for spectators. 
</P>
