<HEADLINE> Pacific Rim Rugby Championship Set for May, June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Pacific Rim Rugby
Championship has been set for May 3-June 20 this year, with a
round-robin, home-and-away competitions, it was announced here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the four-team tournament are Japan, the United
States, defending champion Canada and last year's runner-up Hong
Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
The annual championship, which goes into the third year, will
be opened on May 3 in Tokyo, with Japan playing Canada.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong, China team will play host here for the matches
against Canada on May 9, the United States on May 16 and Japan on
May 23.
</P>
<P>
In June this year, the team will visit Japan, Canada and the
United States for three away matches.
</P>
<P>
The team with the highest points accumulated from the
championship will win the title.
</P>
<P>
During the championship matches in Hong Kong, two exhibition
matches will be played between China's national team and the local
Asian Dragons team.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Hong Kong Rugby Football Union hoped to
impress the Amateur Sports Federation and Olympic Committee of
Hong Kong, China with their players' performance so that the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region will be entered by the local
sports governing body in the Asian Games rugby tournament in
Bangkok. 
</P>
