<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed Thursday mixed on late buying
interest in bluechips like Telekom Malaysia ahead of a public
holiday Friday.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications counters received a boost after a
government's decision to increase foreign participation in
telecommunications firms up to 61 percent from the present 49
percent.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index recovered
3.14 points to 625.97, the all-share Emas Index added 0.91 of a
point to 157.55, the Second Board eased 0.05 of a point to 135.34
and the Industrial Index was 13.17 points lower at 1,148.06.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 310 to 294 while 160 counters were
unchanged and 151 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was at 113.242 million shares worth 297.403
million ringgit (about 80.162 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover was marginally higher at 105.695
million shares worth 284.599 million ringgit (about 76.71 million
U.S. dollars) from 101.513 million shares valued at 253.383
million ringgit (about 68.297 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board volume dropped to 7.547 million shares worth
12.804 million ringgit (about 3.451 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 8.317 million shares valued at 16.205 million ringgit
(about 4.367 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals shrank to 67.784 million shares worth 164.566
million ringgit (about 44.357 million U.S. dollars) from 113.253
million shares valued at 277.531 million ringgit (about 74.806
million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 7.819
million shares traded, industrial products 9.003 million shares,
construction 8.604 million shares, trading/service 28.838 million
shares, infrastructure 931,000 shares, finance 20.130 million
shares, hotels 467,000 shares, properties 11.471 million shares,
plantation 5.904 million shares, mining 561,000 shares, trusts
64,000 shares, closed/fund 192,000 shares and loans 11.709 million
shares. 
