<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang, a leading industrial
center in northeast China, plans to sell 1,000 state-owned
enterprises to foreign and domestic buyers, according to a
provincial government official.
</P>
<P>
He noted the figure will represent the largest number of state
enterprises to be sold to date.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises on offer include profitable small- to medium-sized
ventures.
</P>
<P>
