Republic shortly, Northern Ireland's republican party Sinn Fein
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The four-strong delegation is on a four-day visit to Northern
Ireland and the Republic this week and will be addressing a
number of meetings on both sides of the border, South African
newspaper The Citizen reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sinn Fein, which invited the group, said it is going to listen
and learn from the South African negotiators who had solved many
prickly issues during their reconciliation talks with the former
apartheid government which led to the 1994 democratic election.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to apply, where practical, those lessons to our
efforts to win for the Irish people a lasting peace," said a Sinn
Fein spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Former ANC secretary-general Cyril Ramaphosa, head of the
delegation, was due to address a meeting in Dublin Friday on
"Ireland-South Africa, the Struggle for peace and Justice", the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The ANC officials, who formed the core of the ANC delegation
in the 1993 Kempton Park talks, are hoped to facilitate talks in
Northern Ireland, where an agreement reached by political parties
on April 10 has to be subjected to a referendum on May 22.
</P>
<P>
Outstanding issues such as the status of political prisoners
and the disarmament of para-military groups, are similar to
matters that had to be dealt with in South Africa before the 1994
all-race election.  
