<HEADLINE> Chirac Calls on Israel to Attain Trust and Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Thursday paid homage to the founders of the State of Israel, but
estimated that the country has yet to win trust and peace with its
Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
In a message sent to his Israeli counterpart Ezer Weizman on
the 50th anniversary of the founding of Israel, Chirac praised
Israel as a country "where the orchards are born out of desert
and where industry, research and science draw the Third
Millennium."
</P>
<P>
He also paid homage to the former leaders of Israel -- David Ben
Gourion, Gola Meir, Manahem Begin, Yitzhak Rabin and Shimon Peres.
</P>
<P>
"But a country should, in my view, still attain the essential:
trust and peace," he said.
</P>
<P>
While promising Israel with "frienship and support" of France,
Chirac called on the young people of Israel to be "the heros of
peace."
</P>
<P>
"Today, through you, it is to the youths of Israel that I wish
to address myself to encourage them to be, with your neighbors and
partners of all times, the heros of peace. You can count on the
friendship and support of France," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chirac failed to mention Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu in his message of congratulations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
