<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices ended mixed on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
(STII) fell by 8.71 points to close at 1493.4 points on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that fears of rising interest rates in the United
States contributed to cautious sentiment. They also said that
activity was thin with many punters staying on the sidelines amid
an absence of market-moving news and ahead of the long weekend.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 93.21 million units, valued
at 185.75 million Singapore dollars (about 116.82 million U.S.
dollars). Advances led declines by 150 to 137, while 304 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 7.22 million units. It was followed by
Tai Sin which had 4.99 million shares traded. Rekapac was next
with 3.75 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture led the gainers of the day as it rose by 30 cents to
finish at 5.75 Singapore dollars. Tan Chong increased by 21 cents
to end at 1.15 Singapore dollars. Elec&AMP;E was up by 15 cents to
close at 5.8 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Gook Wood was the biggest loser as it declined
by 18 dollars to end at 20 Singapore dollars. Yamma fell by 8.7
dollars to close at 1.5 U.S. dollars, while Creative 50 was down
by 1.4 dollars to finish at 32.9 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
