<HEADLINE> French Socialists Welcome OECD Suspension of Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- France's ruling Socialist Party
Thursday welcomed the decision by the Organization for Economic
Cooperation and Development (OECD) to suspend its talks on
liberalizing investments among its member countries.
</P>
<P>
In a communique, the party described as "a failure for the
defenders of ultra-liberalism" the decision by OECD on Tuesday to
suspend talks on the Agreement on Multilateral Investment, which
aims to lift barriers on investment among the 29 members of the
organization.
</P>
<P>
"The Socialist Party is delighted that the firmness shown by
the French government allowed the protection of the great
objectives of our country: cultural exception, continuation of
European construction, rejection of social and environmental
dumping and dismantlement of American laws of d'Amato and
Helms-Burton," it said.
</P>
<P>
It also called for vigilance to ensure that globalization
should not become "standardization," and liberalization not become
the synonym of "generalized impoverishment at the profit of a
smallest number of people." 
</P>
</TEXT>
