<HEADLINE> Angola, Portugal Seal Deal on Fishery Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Angola and Portugal signed an
agreement here Wednesday on fishery cooperation, under which the
two countries will concentrate first on professional education,
scientific research and institutional construction in the sector.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Minister of Fisheries Fatima Jardim and visiting
Portuguese State Secretary for Fisheries Sousa Vasconcelos signed
the agreement on behalf of their respective governments, the
Angola News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sousa said after the signing ceremony that the Portuguese
government is willing to help Angola solve the problems left from
the civil war on the basis of mutual trust.
</P>
<P>
He believed the prospects for bilateral cooperation in the
fishery field will be broad.
</P>
<P>
Jardim hailed the agreement as opening "a new era for
bilateral development".
</P>
<P>
Sousa concluded his three-day visit in Angola early Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
He said to the press before his departure that fishery
cooperation between the two countries have enjoyed much
development in the past 10 years, when Portugal invested a
total of two million Escudo (about 13,000 US Dollars) for
professional education and scientific research in this regard.
</P>
