<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets U.S. Secretary Of State (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Both sides agreed that China and the United States share common
interests and have cooperated on the issue of countering the Asian
economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Talking about China's entry to the World Trade Organization,
Zhu said that, as a large country with 1.2 billion population and
the 10th largest country of trade in the world, China needs the
WTO. But, at the same time, the WTO also needs China if it hopes
to become a complete world multilateral trade mechanism.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said China, as a developing country, has lowered its
tariffs five times and is committed to lowering the duties even
further. Meanwhile, China has made great effort in opening up its
market and improving its system of foreign trade, he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said he hoped that the American side would truly understand
the situation in China, which is a developing country, and take a
practical and flexible attitude so that an early agreement can be
reached on China's entry into the WTO. This would be beneficial to
all sides, he added.
</P>
