<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rebound in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rebounded technically
in Tokyo Thursday with the key Nikkei index recovering above
15,500 points after sharp falls in the pervious trading days.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 245.83 points or 1.60
percent to close at 15,641.26.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, advanced 22.08 points or 1.34 percent to
1,222.98.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section fell to an estimated 340 million
shares from Tuesday's 400 million shares. The market was closed
Wednesday for a national holiday.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was Thursday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei index recouped some of the more than 600 points lost
Monday and Tuesday, but trading was dull most of the day, traders
said.
</P>
<P>
Many players took a break for Japan's "Golden Week" holiday
period, which began Wednesday and lasts through Tuesday, they
said. The market will be closed Monday and Tuesday next week.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 issues listed on the First Section, gainers
outpaced losers 758 to 338, with 140 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
