<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Food Processor in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Qishan County, in northwest China's
Shaanxi Province, has emerged as a major snack food processing
center in northwest China, with last year's added processing value
topping 580 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Qishan, one of the 500 major cotton and grain production bases
in China, produces 200,000 tons of grain annually, half of them
being wheat.
</P>
<P>
Qishan and south China's Guangdong Province opened the nation's
first instant noodle packaging line in the county in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The county's 70-odd food processing plants currently process
over 100,000 tons of grain and oil annually. Nineteen ventures
currently produces 18 million cases of instant noodles
annually. Related ventures employ 15,000 workers, both urban and
rural. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
