<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guilin-Japan Air Route Begins Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- An air route linking the major
Chinese tourist city of Guilin with Fukuoka, Japan, opened on
April 28. It is Guilin's first international air route.
</P>
<P>
Operated by China Southern Airlines, the four-hour flight is
offered every Tuesday and Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The airline now is flying Boeing 777 and Boeing 767 aircraft to
cope with high demand on the route.
</P>
<P>
Guilin, in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, is well-known
for the scenic Lijiang River and its picturesque mountains.
</P>
<P>
Fukuoka is one of the four leading industrial areas in Japan as
well as a major tourist region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
