<HEADLINE> NPC Delegation to Visit Latin American Nations: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Chinese
National People's Congress (NPC), led by Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman
of the NPC Standing Committee, will pay an official good-will
visit to Brazil, Chile and Peru from May 8 to 19.
</P>
<P>
It was announced by Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu
Bangzao at a regular press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Tian and his party will be there as guest of the Chamber of
Deputies of Brazil, the Senate of Chile, and the Congress of Peru,
according the spokesman. 
</P>
