<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets U.S. Secretary Of State  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Albright stressed that President Clinton hopes the United
States and China will proceed on the basis of Jiang's highly
successful 1997 visit to the United States and engage in joint
efforts to ensure the success of the Beijing summit.
</P>
<P>
She said the United States hopes to consolidate its
relationship with China in order to further efforts to establish a
constructive strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
Both President Clinton and President Jiang are the first
leaders in their respective countries to fully understand the
importance of the partnership to both bilateral relations and the
world situation, said Albright. She also pointed to the need for
the United States and China to improve all aspects of bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Albright noted that she has exchanged views concerning
preparations of President Clinton's China visit, and engaged in
in-depth discussions covering a wide range of issues concerning
Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Secretary of State has had meetings with Premier Zhu
Rongji and Vice-Premier Qian Qichen.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and Albright held talks on
Wednesday and signed an agreement for the establishment of a
direct secure telephone link between Washington and Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Albright arrived in Beijing on Wednesday for a two-day visit at
the invitation of Tang. 
</P>
