<HEADLINE> China to Host Natural Gas Vehicle Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- An international natural gas
vehicle and equipment show will be held in Haikou, the capital of
China's southernmost island province in November, according to
today's China Youth Daily.
</P>
<P>
Some 5,700 Chinese taxis use natural gas, including liquid
petroleum gas. The paper reported that natural gas is extensively
used by taxi fleets in Chongqing, Harbin, Tianjin, Beijing,
Haikou, Shenzhen and other cities.
</P>
<P>
China has established a national coordination group to promote
the use of natural gas in vehicles, according to the daily. The
article also pointed out the vast potential for international
cooperation and investment in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Foreign companies will be allowed to participate in redesigning
existing vehicles for the use of natural, or to directly build
vehicles which burn the fuel. 
