<HEADLINE> 4 Women Killed by unidentified Gunmen in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Four women of a family were
killed and two others seriously injured in a village household
when some unidentified gunmen opened fire at them early Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan, the
tragedy happened at around 05:00 Thursday morning in a village
called Taragewali in Sheikhpura, some 150 kilometers northwest of
the Punjab provincial capital of Lahore.
</P>
<P>
The report said that three armed men scaled the walls of a
house in Taragewali village, woke up the inmates and asked them to
handover their valuables. But when one of the ladies resisted, the
gunmen opened fire at them indiscriminately, killing four women on
the spot and injuring two others.
</P>
<P>
The outlaws fled the scene as neighbors heard the gunshots and
rushed out.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the local authorities also rushed to the village
 to investigate the accident. 
