<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High-Tech Company Hires Managers at Top Salaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The collectively-owned Dongjiang
Group, a high-tech enterprise in northeast China's Liaoning
Province, posed a challenge to state-owned enterprises by hiring
managers at high salary.
</P>
<P>
The company employed five senior executives recently, including
a vice-president, a vice-president in charge of the group's
marketing, a general manager, an accounting manager and a
technology manager of its subsidiary, Dongjiang Industrial Corp.
</P>
<P>
The annual salary for the five executives is 1.1 million yuan,
accounting for 50 percent of the company's wages. Moreover, the
salary of 200,000 yuan a year is 10 times that of managers of
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
So far, four of the five managers have taken office, and the
technology manager is expected to start soon.
</P>
<P>
Dongjiang Group is a developer of software and a producer of
magnetic cards and intelligent cards, said Li Peiying, chairman
and general manager of the Dongjiang Group.
</P>
<P>
He said the Dongjiang Group has adopted a 4-3-3 distribution
system of profits among the group, branch company and individual
employees. It means that the group takes 40 percent of the net
profit that an individual employee has made, and the rest will be
divided equally between the company he belongs to and the employee
himself.
</P>
<P>
"This distribution system is helpful to encouraging us to work
hard as we can, and enhance the competitiveness of my company,"
said Che Jianhua, chief accountant of Dongjiang Group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
