<HEADLINE> Private Firms Establish Shanghai Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Private companies in Shanghai
has established an association as a bridge providing direct
links to local authorities and other sectors, as well as a media
section to coordinate related activities.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Private Economic Park Entrepreneurs Association
was established by five major private industrial parks. The new
association's membership includes the city's 87 private industrial
parks.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the city now has more than 74,000
private companies with over 150,000 individual investors. Some 80
percent of the firms are located in private industrial parks.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's private entrepreneurs have consistently cited
numerous problems, including the inability to compete with firms
involving other types of ownership on an equal footing,
difficulties in obtaining loans and obtaining approval to expand
their business scopes, and excessive fees and levies.
</P>
<P>
The association will operate in accordance with the principle
of presenting common problems to the concerned departments, and
extending great effort to establish a unified orderly market for
the private industrial parks. 
</P>
