<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 30 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 experts from home
and abroad have gathered in an international symposium in Shanghai
to make suggestions on how to decorate the city with sculptures.
</P>
<P>
The symposium, the first of its kind in the city, opened
Wednesday and focused on the relationship among urban
construction, sculptures and the environment. The experts --
specialists in sculpture, architecture, and horticulture -- come
from such countries as the United States, France, Germany,
Britain, Japan and Norway. Some of them are famous artists in
international sculpture and environmental art.
</P>
