<HEADLINE> Xi'an Aircraft Penetrates International Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Xi'an Aircraft Industry (Group)
Co. Ltd. in northwest China's Shaanxi Province has won orders on
the international market.
</P>
<P>
The company signed contracts with a French aerospace company
involving outer wing casings for 110 ATR42 planes. It previously
manufactured 44 similar casings for the company.
</P>
<P>
The company gained an initial share of the North American
aircraft parts market in the 1980s. In 1994, Xi'an Aircraft signed
inked a contract to provided U.S.-based Boeing with 1,500 vertical
tail sections for Boeing 737-700s.
</P>
<P>
The company has turned to Europe for expanded development in
recent years, and in 1994 signed a contract to produce synthetic
materials for a German aerospace company. as well as a contract to
supply an Italian aerospace company with 200 aircraft fuselages
for ATR72 aircraft.
</P>
<P>
It has invested 300 million yuan and 20 million US dollars to
upgrade 500 sets of equipment over the past decade, in addition to
importing 70 technological items for the production of advanced
aircraft.
</P>
<P>
It has annual exports of 20 million US dollars and ranks as the
nation's leading aerospace manufacturer. 
