<DOCNO> XIE19980430.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portable Computer Prices Fall with Chip Cuts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Computer chip price cuts by
Intel Corp. have heralded a new round of falling notebook PC
prices in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Two notebook makers, Acer and Winbook, slashed prices on the
same day that Intel cut costs on its mobile Pentium MMX and
Pentium II chips.
</P>
<P>
Intel launched the two mobile Pentium processors at the
beginning of April. By the end of the month the prices of the two
models were lowered by eight to 15 percent. The cuts of older
Pentium models were up to more than 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Following the chip price cuts, the two notebook makers lowered
the prices of their low-end products by 20 percent. One model, for
instance, was cut from 1,499 U.S. dollars to 1,199 dollars. The
high-end portables were also cut by seven percent.
</P>
<P>
Traditionally, laptops were among the most profitable segments
of the PC market. When makers of desktop PCs were slashing prices
below 2,000 U.S. dollars, notebook makers were still getting 6,000
to 7,000 dollars. Those days ended in 1997, when desktop PCs
costing less than 1,000 dollars suddenly grabbed about one-third
of the consumer market in the United States. Laptop prices dropped
below 2,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The changing market had affected the earnings of both chip and
computer makers. Intel's earnings dropped by 27 percent in the
first quarter this year from the fourth quarter 1997. Industry
analysts said that the chipmaking giant suffered from a failure to
compete aggressively at the low end of the market. The chip price
cuts indicate that Intel has been learning from the lesson.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Hewlett-Packard also cut prices on notebook
models using MMX chip, to make room for Pentium II models.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that if Intel could not increase demand for
high-powered systems, it was going to be a tough four to six
quarters for PC industry as a whole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980430.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
