<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong-based New World
Development Co. Ltd. has just opened its sixth general chain store
in inland China in Ningbo, a major port city in east China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The Ningbo New World General Merchandise Store, located in
downtown Ningbo, has five floors covering a total of 10,000 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
The group has also invested in general merchandise stores in
Wuhan, Shenyang, Wuxi, Harbin and Tianjin, with related facilities
covering a total of 58,500 square meters.
</P>
<P>
New World is currently carrying out a development plan calling
for additional chain stores in other cities to provide good
conditions, including Beijing, Qingdao and Dalian.
</P>
<P>
The total floor space for New World's general merchandise
supermarkets and shopping centers in inland areas is expected to
reach 240,000 square meters by the end of the century
</P>
<P>
New World Co. Ltd., a major enterprise in Hong Kong with total
assets of 108.4 billion Hong Kong dollars, focuses on the the
property, hotel, infrastructure and telecommunications sectors.
The group's 1997 business volume approached 19.98 billion Hong
Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
The group entered China in the early 1980s with extensive
investments in wide-ranging fields. New World has since providing
funding of over 20 billion yuan for 100-odd projects.
</P>
<P>
Ningbo, one of China's 14 open coastal cities, ranks 27th on
the list of China's top 50 cities in terms of investment
potential. The city has an annual total consumer goods retail
sales volume of over 30 billion yuan. 
</P>
