<HEADLINE> Manufacturing Firms Benefit from Loosened Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- China's manufacturing firms have
witnessed rapid development in export since the country loosened
approval conditions and streamlined applications procedures for
these firms to gain import and export rights, said today's China
Daily.
</P>
<P>
With another 2,000-plus manufacturing enterprises obtaining
foreign trade rights in 1997, there had been 8,000 company members in
the category by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The number of enterprises whose self-conducted export volume
exceeded ten million US dollars rose by 71 to 487 last year, with
their total export volume reaching 14.47 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A survey made by the State Trade and Economic Commission on
4,700 enterprises covering 13 sectors show that of these
companies' 38.5 billion US dollars of total foreign trade volume
in 1997, their self-conducted export amounted to as high as 20.3
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The paper noted that great vigor will be required if these
manufacturing enterprises are to compete directly in the
international market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
