<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy: New Balkan Conflict Must be Prevented </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro said Wednesday that he hoped the Rome meeting of the
six-nation Contact Group on the former Yugoslavia would find a way
to prevent Kosovo becoming another bloody Balkan conflict.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in Luca, a Tuscan town, as the Contact Group met in
Rome to discuss ways of easing tensions in Kosovo, Scalfaro said
Italy and other group members were firmly on the side of peace.
</P>
<P>
"I don't know what can be achieved at the meeting in Rome," the
president admitted. "But we are present with our intelligence and
our hearts to stop the lighting of another fire that no one knows
where it might lead."
</P>
<P>
Delegations from the six nations forming the contact group on
the former Yugoslavia are meeting at the foreign ministry
Wednesday to discuss ways to establish dialogue between Serbian
leaders and ethnic Albanians in the province.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo is a Serbian province with an ethnic Albanian
majority. Conflicts between Serb police and ethnic Albanians
demanding independence from Serbia have reportedly killed at least
80 people since February this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
