<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Prepares Flood Prevention Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong province is
well prepared for flood prevention efforts along the Yellow River,
the second largest river in China, according to the local
government.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to invest 50 million yuan in 25
infrastructure construction projects along the river, including
the reinforcement of dikes and rechanneling projects. Some 50
percent of the total funding has been allocated to date.
</P>
<P>
An overall check of flood control facilities, conducted in
March, has uncovered possibly dangerous areas which the province
is currently repairing.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River was prone to endemic flooding which resulted
in heavy losses of both life and property prior to the founding of
New China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
However, the past 48 years has been relatively free from major
disasters or losses along the river thanks to the efforts of local
people and governments at all levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
