<HEADLINE> Indonesia's net Foreign Reserves rise to 14.31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Net International
Reserves (NIR) went up slightly April 24, 1998 to reach 14.312
billion U.S. dollars compared to 13.57 billion dollars reported on
April 17.
</P>
<P>
According to a press statement issued Wednesday by the Bank
Indonesia (BI), the central bank, the country's gross foreign
assets rose to 17.8 billion U.S. dollars, up from 17 billion
dollars over the same period.
</P>
<P>
"The increase is due to export revenues and the disbursement of
standby loans," said the statement which was available to Xinhua
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The country's net domestic assets were valued at 38.56 trillion
rupiah (4.8 billion U.S. dollars) on April 24, up from 32.88
trillion rupiah on April 17. 
