<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina Floods Aggravate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The emergency situation
caused by floods in the north-east part of Argentina continues to
aggravate as the rains keep on.
</P>
<P>
The water level of the Parana River is still climbing in the
provinces of Chaco, Corrientes, Entre Rios, Santa Fe and Formosa
where the populations have been evacuated, the Argentine Naval
Prefecture said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The flood peak in the river surpassed 8.05 meters on Wednesday
in part of the province of Corrientes. The normal level in that
part is 3.20 meters.
</P>
<P>
The river's water level reached 8.05 meters once in the great
1905 inundation, and the highest level was 9.04 meters registered
in the floods of 1982-1983.
</P>
<P>
The floods have extended to some cities in the provinces of
Buenos Aires and Patagonia, where many people have also been
evacuated.
</P>
<P>
The Naval Prefecture predicted on Wednesday that the climatic
conditions will continue in the coming days, and the flood of the
Parana River will increase in the next weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
