<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Sees Many Industrial Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Industrial accidents have killed
2,020 Bulgarians in 156,000 incidents over the past 10 years,
according to statistics from the Confederation of Independent
Trade Unions in Bulgaria (CITUB).
</P>
<P>
Some 1,038 people became permanently disabled and over 500
people contracted occupational diseases.
</P>
<P>
Over 400,000 people are working in dangerous conditions, CITUB
Chairman Dr Zhelyuazko Hristov told a news conference Wednesday,
April 29, the third international day of mourning those who died
or were permanently injured in industrial accidents.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government should urgently pass legislation on
healthy and safe labor conditions, as well as a package of laws on
social and health insurance. 
</P>
