<HEADLINE> New World Group to Increase Investments in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 30 (Xinhua) --Hong Kong-based New World Group
plans to invest between 3-4 billion yuan in infrastructure
construction projects in north China's Shanxi Province over the
next three years.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Kar-shun, chairman of the board of Hong Kong New World
(China) Development Corporation, led a seven-member company
fact-finding delegation to Shanxi between April 24-26. The
delegation signed contracts or agreements for six projects
involving total investments of one billion yuan, according to
local sources.
</P>
<P>
The list of projects includes construction of the 180 million
yuan Xihuayuan Residential Complex in the provincial capital of
Taiyuan, an aquarium park which will require a total investment of
60 million yuan. and a power plant costing 4.1 billion yuan. New
World will provide 49 percent of the funding.
</P>
<P>
The New World Group focuses on real estate development, hotel
investments, infrastructure construction projects, engineering and
telecommunications. The group has invested in inland areas since
the 1980s and currently operates offices in over a dozen Chinese
cities. The group is currently involved in domestic projects
valued at over 100 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi, widely known as the "Sea of Coal", has proven coal
reserves of over 260.87 billion tons, or close to one third of the
national total. 
</P>
