<HEADLINE> China Introduces Mass Production of White Blood Cells </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 30 (Xinhua) -- China initiated the mass
production of genetically engineered pharmaceutical for increasing
white blood cells.
</P>
<P>
The new pharmaceutical was developed by geneticists in
Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
China is the third country in the world with the capacity to
mass produce the new pharmaceutical, following the United States
and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The product is used for the treatment of tumors and leukopenic
cases resulting from which leukemia patients react to chemical
therapy. The product is one of the most popular genetically
engineered pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
The product -- Recombination Human Granular Colony Stimulating
Factor, the fourth genetically engineered product pharmaceutical
developed in China, is produced by Hangzhou Jiuyuan Genetic
Engineering Company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
