<DOCNO> XIE19980430.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Styrene Project Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Yangba Styrene Project,
China's largest styrene project, has commenced full-scale
operations in Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, established by the Yangtze Petrochemical
Corporation and German-based BASF Group, will produce styrene
products using domestic raw materials and advanced technology
provided by the latter.
</P>
<P>
The project, completed at a cost of two billion yuan, will
produce 120,000 tons of styrene and 100,000 tons of polystyrene
annually.
</P>
<P>
Polystyrene is widely used in the production of household
appliances, electronic products and various other daily-use items.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the project was completed over a two year
period ending in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
