Shanghai has also joined other parts of China in launching
cooperative ventures in the financial, technological, tourism and
agricultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
The city's research institutes have provided more than 6,100
research findings to underdeveloped areas since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has adopted preferential lending policies
for cooperative projects and has establishment a special 300
million yuan fund to support related programs.
</P>
<P>
A municipal plan calls for the industrial sector to invest
1.5 billion yuan in other parts of the country during 1998.
</P>
