<HEADLINE> Bulgaria, Norway Sign Military Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Defense Minister Georgi
Ananiev and his Norwegian counterpart Dag Jostein Fjaervoll have
signed an agreement on the military cooperation between the two
nations.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact signed in Sofia on Wednesday, the two nations
will exchange military experts and officers and develop concrete
programs for military cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Ananiev said he commended Norway's stand to back the "Open
Door" policy adopted by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) at the Madrid summit.
</P>
<P>
He said Bulgaria would be included in the second wave of
admissions to NATO.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Norwegian defense minister said that the two
ministers had put the prospects of joining peace-keeping
operations in Europe and other parts of the world on their agenda.
</P>
<P>
He said the Treaty of Conventional Armed Forces in Europe could
serve as a good basis for further promotion of contacts in this
regard.
</P>
<P>
Fjaervoll arrived here on Tuesday. He is scheduled to meet
Colonel General Miho Mihov, chief of the General Staff of the
Bulgarian Army, Foreign Minister Nadezhda Mihailova and Prime
Minister Ivan Kostov on Wednesday. 
</P>
