<HEADLINE> Capital Has 3,000 Citizens' Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- China's capital has set up some
3,000 citizens' schools with an enrollment of more than 700,000
people, in a bid to promote cultural and ethic progress.
</P>
<P>
The citizens' schools, which were launched in 1991 and
immediately received an enthusiastic response from the general
public, have gradually spread to every street in the city.
</P>
<P>
The students, who are mainly retired people, have lessons once
a month mainly on the country's policies, laws and some other basic
items of knowledge.
</P>
<P>
The schools also accept younger students, locally-stationed
soldiers and workers from elsewhere. 
</P>
