<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Pre-match favorite Jimmy White's
world title hopes were dashed by Ronnie O'Sullivan in a
quarter-final clash in the World Snooker Championships in
Sheffield on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the second session on Wednesday White threatened to
stage a remarkable recovery after O'Sullivan had established a 7-1
lead in the opening session.
</P>
<P>
With breaks of 63, 58, 54, 80 and 62, White moved to within
three frames of the world number seven at 9-6 but O'Sullivan won
the crucial final frame of the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
White took the third frame of the evening session with a break
of 72 but O'Sullivan claimed the frame he required for victory
with a 118 clearance.
</P>
<P>
O'Sullivan will next face John Higgins in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
On the other table Mark Williams defeated Peter Ebdon to set up
a semi-final duel with Ken Doherty.
</P>
<P>
