<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Increases Earnings From Marine Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The output value from marine
industry in south China's Guangdong Province has soared to 85
billion yuan (1.02 billion US dollars), with the figure ranking
first in the nation and accounting for 11.6 percent of the
provincial GDP.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's extensive coastline stretches 5,782 km and the
province has 1,431 islands. The province currently ranks third in
the nation in terms of ocean resources.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the province used 139,000 ha of sea area for
aquatics production and led the nation in output of prawns
and shellfish.
</P>
<P>
The province recorded 1997 earnings of 29.5 billion yuan (3.55
billion US dollars) from ocean tourism and 6.38 billion yuan from
ship repairs, with respective figures representing 430-fold and
320-fold increases of 1990.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong has also witnessed development in ocean-related areas
such as oil and gas exploration, transportation and salt
production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
