<HEADLINE> Beijing Focuses on Greening Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has extended great
efforts to develop landscaping bases on science and technology,
with related efforts playing an increasingly important role in
beautifying the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Local scientists and technician have developed and raised
millions of plants readily adapted to the local environment, and
have at the same time publicized technology for the prevention of
plant diseases and insect infestations.
</P>
<P>
Local gardeners have conducted extensive research concerning
the urban environment, and have scored remarkable achievements in
developing new varieties of plants and propagation technology.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has fewer plant varieties due to long cold winter and
strong winds in spring and autumn.
</P>
<P>
Local scientists and technicians have provided over 150
varieties of plants for the city over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Beijing plans to increase its forest coverage rate to 40
percent and per capita landscaped areas to eight sq.m. by the
end of the century.
</P>
<P>
The city currently has 120 parks, a tree and grass coverage of
33 percent and a per-capita green space of seven sq.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
