<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Quarter Rise in Hubei Import-Export Volume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The import-export volume for
central China's Hubei Province grew by 16 percent to
reach 752 million US dollars for the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Exports stood at 631 million US dollars, up 18 percent on the
1997 period and 5.2 percentage points higher than the national
average. Imports grew by eight percent to 122 million US dollars
during the period.
</P>
<P>
Hubei has responded to the financial crisis in Southeast Asia,
by readjusting its export structure, increasing exports of
machinery and electronic products, as well as telecommunications
and power plant equipment, according to Fan Kaishi, director of
the Hubei Department Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Hubei's exports countries in the European Union grew by 48
percent, with export to the United States up 5.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Declining costs of imports from Southeast Asia has resulted in
increased imports of advanced technology, complete sets of
equipment and rubber used to upgrade state-owned enterprises in
the first quarter of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
