<HEADLINE> Top-Seeded Rusedski Falls in Munich Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Greg Rusedski suffered a
surprise defeat in the first round of the Munich Open tennis
tournament on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Briton was knocked out 6-4, 6-0 by little-known German
Oliver Gross.
</P>
<P>
Three other seeds also tumbled in second-round matches,
including Rusedski's compatriot Tim Henman, seeded fourth, who
fell 6-3, 6-1 to Swede Tomas Nydahl.
</P>
<P>
French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil, the third seed,
lost 7-6, 6-3 to veteran Swede Magnus Gustafsson.
</P>
<P>
Last year's winner Mark Philippoussis of Australia, seeded
fifth this year, was the last casualty of the day, losing 6-4
7-6 to unfancied Frenchman Nicolas Escude.
</P>
<P>
Swede Thomas Enqvist, seeded seventh, will take on eighth seed
Andre Agassi of the United States on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
