<HEADLINE> Johnson, Bailey May Clash Again at Goodwill Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Michael Johnson and Donovan
Bailey may compete against each other again this summer as part of
the Goodwill Games in New York.
</P>
<P>
Harvey Schiller, president of Turner Sports, said that there
was a "good possibility" of a rematch of the 150-meter race at
Toronto last year where Johnson pulled up injured after 70 meters.
</P>
<P>
As there are many details to be arranged, Schiller said that
the race could be set in a few weeks.
</P>
<P>
Johnson won the 200 and 400 meters golds at the 1996 Olympic
Games. He also holds the 200 meters world record. Bailey is the
1996 Olympic 100 meters gold medalist and world record holder.
</P>
</TEXT>
