<HEADLINE> Wall Street Gains More Lost Ground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Blue-chip stocks on Wall Street
halted a week-long slump Wednesday, showing modest gains in quiet
trading.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 52.56 points to 8,951.52.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by nearly a 2-to-1
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 638.09
million shares as against 677.74 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The broad market posted modest gains for the second straight
session, recovering more ground.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 9.51 to 1,094.62, and
the NYSE composite index rose 4.74 to 568.30.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 19.87 to 1,851.64.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 4.44 to 476.98,
and the American Stock Exchange composite index rose 9.29 to
742.32.  
</P>
</TEXT>
