<DOCNO> XIE19980430.0317 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African President Stresses Importance of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The visiting South African
President Nelson Mandela stressed the importance of regional
integration in southern Africa in Luanda Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mutual reliance in economy has made the southern African
nations aware of the importance of the regional integration, said
President Mandela who is on his first state visit to Angola.
</P>
<P>
The president said that countries in southern Africa have
taken the region as a whole in considering their needs in trade
and development.
</P>
<P>
The South African industrialists accompanying President
Mandela held a meeting with the Angolan entrepreneurs.
Addressing the meeting, President Mandela said that such thinking
has led to the establishment of the Southern African Development
Community and made it an institution helpful for the economic
development of all its member states.
</P>
<P>
The South African leader said that the meeting between the
business people from the two countries is "significant" for both
the development of southern Africa and the bilateral relations
between the two nations in the future.
</P>
<P>
South African businesses have participated in the
reconstruction of Angola. The future is broad and bright for the
cooperation of South Africa and Angola in industry, banking,
petroleum, fishery and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The president said that both Angola and South Africa have
great potential, which has not been developed due to colonialist
control and apartheid.
</P>
<P>
"South African companies wish to lose no opportunity to expand
trade and investment ties between the two countries," said
Mandela.
</P>
<P>
President Mandela arrived in Luanda Wednesday for a two-day
visit to Angola at the invitation of Angolan President Jose Dos
Santos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
